New Party Formed in Japan
TOKYO , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Five members of Japan 's House of Councillors ( Upper House ) formed a new party Monday in a bid to protect their political independence , Kyodo News reported .
The five legislators belonging to the " Sangiin no Kai " parliamentary group in Japan 's upper chamber filed papers with the Tokyo Election Administration Commission to set up the new party , called the " Sangiin Club " .
The new party , to be led by Motoo Shiina , cited reform of the upper house as its goal and will not force its members to fall in step with one another on specific policies , the report said .
